data.enText: the act or process of making sth that is new, or of causing sth to exist that did not exist before

data.chText: 他从1989年公司成立以来，就一直在那里工作。
data.enText: He had been with the company since its creation in 1989.
a thing that sb has made, especially sth that shows ability or imagination

data.chText: 这蛋糕是用松糕、奶油和水果制作的，又好吃，又好看。
data.enText: The cake was a delicious creation of sponge, cream and fruit.

data.chText: （尤指《圣经》所述由上帝）创造天地
data.enText: the making of the world, especially by God as described in the Bible
the world and all the living things in it

means: (尤指《圣经》所述由上帝)创造天地

tr: the act of starting something for the first time
example: she looked forward to her initiation as an adult
the foundation of a new scientific society

tr: an artifact that has been brought into existence by someone
the event that occurred at the beginning of something
example: from its creation the plan was doomed to failure
they study the evolution of the universe

value.def: In many religions, creation is the making of the universe, earth, and creatures by God.

example.ex: ...the Creation of the universe as told in Genesis Chapter One...
example.tran: 《创世记》第一章所述的上帝创造世界万物

example.ex: For the first time since creation, the survival of the Earth is entirely in our hands.
example.tran: 自宇宙形成以来，地球的存亡第一次完全掌握在我们手中。

value.tran: (许多宗教中指上帝的)创世，创造天地

value.def: People sometimes refer to the whole universe as creation .
You can refer to something that someone has made as a creation, especially if it shows skill, imagination, or artistic ability.

example.ex: The bathroom is entirely my own creation...
example.tran: 浴室完全是由我设计的。

example.ex: Featured are both his classics and his latest creations...
example.tran: 他的经典作品和最新创作都很独特。

example.ex: You'll be amazed at the culinary creations possible in a Dutch oven.
example.tran: 荷兰烤箱能够做的食物之多会让你感到惊奇。

value.tran: 创造物;(尤指)艺术作品，富于想象力的作品
